Đặt vấn đề¶

Dataset "credit_card_clients.xls" l b d liu c nhm tc gi la chn cho d n. B d liu ny cha thng tin lin quan n thanh ton v cc c im ca hn 30,000 khch hng trong khong thi gian t thng 4 n thng 9 ca nm 2005. Nhim v bao gm khm ph tp d liu v to mt m hnh n gin phc v cho mc tiu ca d n l d on kh nng thanh ton khon vay ca khch hng trong thng tip theo (thng 10/2005).

thc hin yu cu ca bi, nhm tc gi tin hnh x l b d liu "credit_card_clients.xls" theo trnh t sau y:

  1. Tm hiu b d liu.
  2. Importing and Loading Data
  3. Data Cleaning
  4. Exploratory Data Analysis
  5. Build Model (nhm xy dng model trong trng hp d liu imbalance v c trng hp resample d liu)

Giải thích thuật ngữ¶

Thut ng "default payment" c hiu l "khng c kh nng thanh ton ng hn" hoc "vi phm ngha v thanh ton". y l tnh trng khi mt ngi khng thc hin thanh ton ng hn theo tha thun hoc hp ng k kt, dn n vic phi tr mt khon pht hoc cc khon li sut pht sinh. Nu trng hp vi phm ny ko di th c th dn n nhng hu qu nghim trng nh mt tn nhim ti cc t chc tn dng v tng nguy c n xu. Nh vy, bindefault payment next monthvi 2 gi tr (1,0) c hiu l:

  • 1: khch hng khng c kh nng thanh ton vo thng tip theo
  • 0: khch hng c kh nng thanh ton vo thng tip theo.

1. Overview¶

B d liu ny cha thng tin v cc khon thanh ton mc nh, cc yu t nhn khu hc, d liu tn dng, lch s thanh ton v bng sao k ha n ca cc khch hng s dng th tn dng Heaven t thng 4 nm 2005 n thng 9 nm 2005.

C tng cng 25 thuc tnh:

  • ID: ID ca mi khch hng

  • LIMIT_BAL: S tin tn dng c cp bng i t (bao gm c nhn v gia nh/th tn dng ph)

  • SEX: Gii tnh

    • 1 = male
    • 2 = female

  • EDUCATION: Trnh hc vn ca khch hng

    • 1 = graduate school
    • 2 = university
    • 3 = high school
    • 4 = others
    • 5 = unknown
    • 6 = unknown

  • MARRIAGE: Tnh trng hn nhn ca khch hng

    • 1 = married
    • 2 = single
    • 3 = others

  • AGE: Tui

  • PAY_0: Tnh trng tr n thng 9/2005

    • -1 = tr ng hn
    • 1 = tr chm mt thng
    • 2 = tr chm hai thng
    • 8 = tr chm tm thng
    • 9 = tr chm t chn thng tr ln

  • PAY_2: Tnh trng tr n thng 8/2005 (m t thnh phn nh trn)

  • PAY_3: Tnh trng tr n thng 7/2005 (m t thnh phn nh trn)

  • PAY_4: Tnh trng tr n thng 6/2005 (m t thnh phn nh trn)

  • PAY_5: Tnh trng tr n thng 5/2005 (m t thnh phn nh trn)

  • PAY_6: Tnh trng tr n thng 4/2005 (m t thnh phn nh trn)

  • BILL_AMT1: Tng sao k ha n thng 9/2005 (i t)

  • BILL_AMT2: Tng sao k ha n thng 8/2005 (i t)

  • BILL_AMT3: Tng sao k ha n thng 7/2005 (i t)

  • BILL_AMT4: Tng sao k ha n thng 6/2005 (i t)

  • BILL_AMT5: Tng sao k ha n thng 5/2005 (i t)

  • BILL_AMT6: Tng sao k ha n thng 3/2005 (i t)

  • PAY_AMT1: S tin tr trc trong thng 9/2005 (i t)

  • PAY_AMT2: S tin tr trc trong thng 8/2005 (i t)

  • PAY_AMT3: S tin tr trc trong thng 7/2005 (i t)

  • PAY_AMT4: S tin tr trc trong thng 6/2005 (i t)

  • PAY_AMT5: S tin tr trc trong thng 5/2005 (i t)

  • PAY_AMT6: S tin tr trc trong thng 4/2005 (i t)

  • default.payment.next.month: Khch hng khng c kh nng thanh ton khon n vo thng 10/2005

    • 1 = c
    • 0 = khng

T bng kt qu ta quan st thy:

  • Bin LIMIT_BAL c gi tr [320, 32000], gi tr min v max c s chnh lch ln.
  • Bin SEX c 2 gi tr l 1-male v 2-female trong phn ln cc quan st c gi tr l 2

  • Bin MARRIAGE c gi tr [1,3], phn ln cc quan st c gi tr l 2 (single)

  • Cc bin BILL_AMTi (i=[1,6]) c khong gi tr rt ln, cc quan st c th c gi tr m hoc dng
  • Cc bin PAY_AMTi (vi i =[1,6]) u c gi tr nh nht bng 0, gi tr ln nht chnh lch tng i ln so vi gi tr min v u > 13000
  • Bin default c 2 gi tr l 0 v 1, d dng quan st thy phn ln cc quan st c gi tr = 0

def kde_plot(columns, title):
    # Set the color palette for the curves
    colors = ['blue', 'green', 'red', 'purple', 'orange', 'gray']
  
    # Create a figure and axes
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize = (12,6))
  
    # Plot the KDE curves
    for i, column in enumerate(columns):
        sns.kdeplot(data[column], color=colors[i], ax=ax, label=column, bw_method = 0.6)
  
    # Set the legend
    ax.legend()
  
    # Set the title and labels
    ax.set_title(title)
    ax.set_xlabel('Values')
    ax.set_ylabel('Density')
  
    # Show the plot
    plt.show()

def remove_outliers(data: pd.DataFrame, feat: str):
      feat_fraud = data[feat]
      q25, q75 = np.percentile(feat_fraud, 25), np.percentile(feat_fraud, 75)
      iqr = q75 - q25
      
      cut_off = iqr * 1.5
      lower, upper = q25 - cut_off, q75 + cut_off
  
      outliers = [x for x in feat_fraud if x < lower or x > upper]
      print(f'S im bt thng cho thuc tnh {feat} trong tp data_train: {len(outliers)}')
  
      return data.drop(data[(data[feat] > upper) | (data[feat] < lower)].index)

def predictProcess(model_type, X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test, **kwargs):
      # Check if model_type is valid
      if model_type not in ('KNN', 'SVC','RandomForest','XGB','Logistic'):
          raise ValueError('Choose one of these models: KNN, SVC, RandomForest, XGB, Logistic')
      
      # Getting the model
      if model_type == 'KNN':
          model = KNeighborsClassifier()
      elif model_type == 'RandomForest':
          model = RandomForestClassifier()
      elif model_type == 'SVC':
          model = SVC()
      elif model_type == 'XGB':
          model = XGBClassifier()
      elif model_type == 'Logistic':
          model = LogisticRegression()
  
      # Fit the model
      model.fit(X_train, y_train)
  
      # Predict
      y_pred_train = model.predict(X_train)
      y_pred_test = model.predict(X_test)
  
      return y_pred_train, y_pred_test
    
  def confusion_heat(y_true, y_pred, ax, title):
      cm = confusion_matrix(y_true,y_pred)
      ax.set_title(title)
      plt.figure(figsize = (4,4))
      sns.heatmap(cm, cmap = 'Greens', linecolor = 'black', linewidth = 1, 
                  annot = True, fmt = '', ax = ax)

classifiers = ['KNN','SVC','RandomForest','XGB','Logistic']
  metrics_result = {}
  
  for classifier in classifiers: 
    time_start = time.time()
    print(f'Prediting by classifier: {classifier} ....')
    y_pred_train, y_pred_test = predictProcess(classifier, X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test)
    print(f'Time consumed: {time.time() - time_start}')
  
    # Metrics
    acc_train = accuracy_score(y_train, y_pred_train) 
    acc_test = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_test)  
    pre_train = precision_score(y_train, y_pred_train)
    pre_test = precision_score(y_test, y_pred_test)
    re_train = recall_score(y_train, y_pred_train)
    re_test = recall_score(y_test, y_pred_test)
    f1_train = f1_score(y_train, y_pred_train)
    f1_test = f1_score(y_test, y_pred_test)
  
    # Confusion matrix
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(1,2, figsize = (10,4))
    confusion_heat(y_train, y_pred_train, axs[0], f'{classifier}: Train_data')
    confusion_heat(y_test, y_pred_test, axs[1], f'{classifier}: Test_data')
    plt.show()
  
    # Store metrics
    if classifier not in metrics_result:
      metrics_result[classifier] = [acc_train, acc_test, pre_train, pre_test, re_train, re_test, f1_train, f1_test]
    
    print('-' * 20)

5.3 Modeling with resampled dataset¶

  • Hm di y s tin hnh chia tp train thnh cc folds, sau tin hnh upsampling cho tp train v nh gi metricprecisioncho mi iteration

  • Trong mi iteration, ta cng tin hnh lun ng thi robust scale ri min max scale (fit_transformtrn tp train,transformtrn tp evaluate)

  • Kt qu tr v l kt qu: accuracy, precision, recall v f1_score tng ng vi tng fold

In [ ]:
def score_model(model, X_train, y_train, cv=None):
      """
      Creates folds manually, and upsamples within each fold.
      Returns an array of validation (precision) scores
      """
      if cv is None:
          cv = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=5, random_state=42, shuffle=True)
  
      smoter = SMOTE(random_state=42)
      
      scores = []
  
      X_train.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)  # Reset indices of X_train
      y_train.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)  # Reset indices of y_train
  
      num_fold = 0
  
      for train_fold_index, val_fold_index in cv.split(X_train, y_train):
          num_fold += 1
          # Get the training data
          X_train_fold, y_train_fold = X_train.iloc[train_fold_index], y_train[train_fold_index]
  
          # Get the validation data
          X_val_fold, y_val_fold = X_train.iloc[val_fold_index], y_train[val_fold_index]
  
          # Robust scale
          X_train_fold_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train_fold[columns_to_scale])
          X_val_fold_scaled = scaler.transform(X_val_fold[columns_to_scale])
  
          # Upsample only the data in the training section
          X_train_fold_scaled_upsample, y_train_fold_upsample = smoter.fit_resample(X_train_fold_scaled,
                                                                                     y_train_fold)
          # Fit the model on the upsampled training data
          model_obj = model().fit(X_train_fold_scaled_upsample, y_train_fold_upsample)
          
          # Prediction
          y_pred_fold = model_obj.predict(X_val_fold_scaled)
  
          # Score the mean of metrics on the (non-upsampled) validation data
          acc = accuracy_score(y_val_fold, y_pred_fold)
          pre = precision_score(y_val_fold, y_pred_fold)
          recall = recall_score(y_val_fold, y_pred_fold)
          f1 = f1_score(y_val_fold, y_pred_fold)
          scores.append({f'fold_{num_fold}':[acc,pre,recall,f1]})
  
      return scores

def distribution_plot(ax, x_value, y_value, x_label, y_label, title):
      """
      Params:
       :x_value(array): 
       :y_value(array):
       :x_label(str): 
       :y_label(str):
       :title(str):
      
      Returns
      """
      sns.kdeplot(x_value, color="r", label=x_label, ax=ax)
      sns.kdeplot(y_value, color="b", label=y_label, ax=ax)
  
      ax.set_title(title)
      ax.legend()
